// Canary — configurable monitoring and alerting system. Watches external
// data sources on a schedule and sends alerts when checks fail or recover.
//
    // monitor.create(CreateMonitorDto)
//   Creates a named monitor in Deno KV. A monitor is the top-level
//   entity representing something you want to watch.
//
    // monitor.list({})
//   Returns all configured monitors for the UI dashboard.
//
    // monitor.get(MonitorIdDto)
//   Returns full detail of a single monitor.
//
    // check.configure(ConfigureCheckDto)
//   Attaches a check to a monitor. Defines the HTTP source, extractor
//   expression, comparator, threshold, cron schedule, and whether to
//   send recovery alerts. Replaces any existing check config.
//
    // check.get(MonitorIdDto)
//   Returns the check configuration for a given monitor.
//
    // schedule.build(ScheduleInputDto)
//   Converts human-friendly time, days, and frequency input into a
//   validated cron string for use in check.configure.
//
    // alert.configure(ConfigureAlertDto)
    //   Attaches typed recipients (sms or email) to a monitor. Replaces
//   any existing alert config.
//
    // alert.get(MonitorIdDto)
//   Returns the alert channel configuration for a given monitor.
//
    // secret.set(SetSecretDto)
//   Stores a named secret value in Deno KV for use by integrations.
//
    // secret.list({})
//   Returns all stored secret key names. Values are never returned.
//
    // secret.delete(SecretKeyDto)
//   Removes a named secret from Deno KV.
//
    // runner.execute(MonitorIdDto)
//   Cron-triggered core loop. Loads monitor, check, and alert configs.
//   Fetches the data source, extracts a numeric value, evaluates the
//   comparator, saves the run result to history, and dispatches alerts
//   if the check fails or recovers.

