[TYP] monitor: Class
    a named monitoring target stored in Deno KV
[TYP] check: Class
    check configuration attached to a monitor
[TYP] schedule: Class
    a validated cron schedule built from human-friendly input
[TYP] alert: Class
    alert channel configuration attached to a monitor
[TYP] secret: Class
    a named secret key-value pair stored in Deno KV
[TYP] source: Class
    abstract data source used to fetch check values
[TYP] extractor: Class
    logic for extracting a numeric value from a source response
[TYP] comparator: Class
    logic for comparing an observed value against a threshold
[TYP] runResult: Class
    the result of a single check execution with pass or fail status
[TYP] alertChannel: Class
    abstract alert dispatch channel supporting sms and email
[TYP] recipient: Class
    a typed alert recipient with a channel type and contact address
[TYP] monitorId: string
    unique identifier for a monitor
[TYP] name: string
    display name of a monitor
[TYP] description: string
    human-readable description of what the monitor is watching
[TYP] url: string
    HTTP endpoint URL for the check data source
[TYP] method: string
    HTTP method for the source request, GET or POST
[TYP] headers: Record<string, string>
    optional HTTP headers to include with the source request
[TYP] body: string
    optional JSON request body for POST source requests
[TYP] expression: string
    dot-notation path to extract a numeric value from the response
[TYP] comparatorOp: string
    comparison operator to apply: lt, gt, lte, gte, or eq
[TYP] threshold: number
    numeric value to compare the observed result against
[TYP] cron: string
    cron expression string defining when the check runs
[TYP] notifyOnRecover: boolean
    whether to send an alert when a failing check passes again
[TYP] observed: number
    the numeric value extracted from the source during a check run
[TYP] passed: boolean
    whether the check passed the configured comparator and threshold
[TYP] secretKey: string
    the name identifier for a stored secret
[TYP] secretValue: string
    the sensitive value of a stored secret
[TYP] alertType: string
    the type of alert channel: sms or email
[TYP] contact: string
    phone number or email address for an alert recipient
[TYP] runId: string
    unique identifier for a single check run
[TYP] timestamp: string
    ISO 8601 timestamp of when a check run occurred
[TYP] timeOfDay: string
    human-readable time for scheduling such as 4:00 PM
[TYP] daysOfWeek: string
    comma-separated days or keyword such as weekdays or daily
[TYP] frequency: string
    schedule frequency keyword such as once, hourly, or daily


[DTO] CreateMonitorDto: name, description
    input for creating a new named monitor
[DTO] MonitorDto: monitorId, name, description
    a resolved monitor with its identifier and display fields
[DTO] MonitorListDto: monitor(s)
    all configured monitors for the UI dashboard
[DTO] MonitorIdDto: monitorId
    input for querying a single monitor by ID
[DTO] ConfigureCheckDto: monitorId, url, method, headers, body, expression,
    comparatorOp, threshold, cron, notifyOnRecover
    input for attaching or replacing a check configuration on a monitor
[DTO] CheckDto: monitorId, url, method, headers, body, expression,
    comparatorOp, threshold, cron, notifyOnRecover
    resolved check configuration for a monitor
[DTO] ScheduleInputDto: timeOfDay, daysOfWeek, frequency
    human-friendly schedule input to convert into a cron expression
[DTO] ScheduleDto: cron
    a validated cron expression generated from human-friendly input
[DTO] ConfigureAlertDto: monitorId, recipient(s)
    input for attaching or replacing alert recipients on a monitor
[DTO] AlertDto: monitorId, recipient(s)
    resolved alert channel configuration for a monitor
[DTO] RecipientDto: alertType, contact
    a single typed alert recipient with channel type and contact
[DTO] SetSecretDto: secretKey, secretValue
    input for storing a named secret value in Deno KV
[DTO] SecretDto: secretKey
    a stored secret represented by its key name only, never its value
[DTO] SecretKeyDto: secretKey
    input for querying or deleting a secret by key name
[DTO] SecretListDto: secret(s)
    all stored secret key names
[DTO] ResponseDto: payload
    raw response payload from an HTTP source request
[DTO] RunResultDto: runId, monitorId, observed, passed, timestamp
    the result of a single check run including observed value and status
